<title>Weather beaten</title>
<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thomasguest/2740477283/" title="Shellfish"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3073/2740477283_b290beb539_m.jpg" width="177" height="240" alt="shellfish" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&amp;#8217;re back from holiday a few days earlier than planned. Even if you&amp;#8217;re camping in a field surrounded by sand-dunes and just a few hundred metres from the &lt;a href="http://www.cornwallbeachguide.co.uk/penwith/gwithian/gwithian.htm"&gt;best beach in the world&lt;/a&gt;, the rain gets to you after a while.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;
     body-boarding, rock-pooling, fighting the waves
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     watching Isobel and Alex ride their bicycles around the campsite
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     reading
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     a &lt;a href="http://www.thealbarestaurant.com/"&gt;memorable meal&lt;/a&gt; in St Ives
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     the &lt;a href="http://www.tate.org.uk/stives/hepworth/"&gt;Barbara Hepworth sculpture garden&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     clear roads, for once
 &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.tate.org.uk/stives/hepworth/"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.tate.org.uk/stives/hepworth/images/garden_in_spring.jpg" alt="Sculpture garden"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not so good:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;
     gusting wind
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     ceaseless rain
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     damp shoes
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     pulled muscle
 &lt;/li&gt;

 &lt;li&gt;
     car trouble
 &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thomasguest/2741314568/" title="Mousehole harbour, in the rain"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3097/2741314568_c62067665a.jpg" width="500" height="165" alt="mousehole" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description>
